3286. Find a Safe Walk Through a Grid


---

1. Problem Statement

You are given an m × n binary grid and an integer health.

You start from the top-left cell (0,0).

Your goal is to reach the bottom-right cell (m−1,n−1).

You can move in 4 directions:

Up

Down

Left

Right


Every time you enter a cell:

If grid[i][j] == 0, health remains the same.

If grid[i][j] == 1, health decreases by 1.


Your health must always remain greater than 0.


Return True if it is possible to reach the destination with health ≥ 1, otherwise return False.


---

